.\" man page for our shell - hsh
.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "Holberton simple_shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.PP
If you run it as
.BR ./hsh
(or any other path), that name shows up as
.BR argv[0]
in errors, same as usual.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a small shell: read a line, split into words, run something. Built-ins stay
in the parent; everything else we look up with
.BR PATH
or treat as a path, then
.BR fork (2)
+
.BR execve (2).
Parent waits on the kid before the next prompt.
.PP
Interactive mode (stdin is a tty): we print a
.B ($)
prompt each time. Non-interactive: no prompt, we quit at EOF on
.B standart
input.
.SH "BUILT-IN COMMANDS"
.TP
.BR exit
Leave the shell. Extra arguments are not requred for this version.
.TP
.BR env
Dump the environment,
.B name=value
one per line.
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
Kids get the same env through
.BR execve;
.B env
just prints it.
.B PATH
is what we use for lookups.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
0 when the main loop ends normally (EOF on stdin);
.B exit
also ends with 0 here.
.SH BUGS
No pipes, no redirects, no real quoting. Not trying to clone
.BR sh.
.SH AUTHOR
See
.B AUTHORS
in the repo root.